lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2495  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors show that slow KAR-mediated postsynaptic responses in MF-CA3 synapses are mediated by GluK2/GluK5 heteromers via sensitivity to UBP310, a compound that was first to be selective for GluK1 or GluK3 containing KARs only. Authors show that UBP310 is an antagonist of GluK2/GluK5 heteromers and not of GluK2 homomeric KARs in a heterologous system. Via activity of the UBP310 compound in GluK1 or GluK3 KO animals the action of UBP310 on GluK2/GluK5 heteromers and not GluK1 or GluK3 containing KARs is confirmed.\n\nNote: Of Gluk5 is it known that it is unable to form functional homopentameric KARs. It is known to form GluK2/GluK5 heteropentamers that represent a large portion of all KAR-mediated responses in the mammalian brain.. Experimental description: \"Mouse parasagittal brain slices of 14- to 21-day-old C57BL/6 wild-type and GluK1 and GluK3 knockout mice were...\"\n- Species of the overexpressed GluK2 and Gluk5 proteins is not stated in the paper. Annotation based on the data obtained with the antagonist in vivo." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_2495" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

